AMUC
----

   The AMiga Users of Calgary, a non-profit Society dedicated to the
Amiga computer, also publishes CDROMs.  These are slightly modified
images of their BBS file system.  Since they run IceBBS software the
CDROM is unique in that it contains IceBBS format description files for
most of the files on the disk.  Their intent is to cut a new CDROM each
time their main hard drive fills up.  The AMUC2: and AMUC3: disks were
released as a two disk set in late December 1994.

     AMUC
     Box 34230
     #19, 1200 - 37th St. S.W.
